                            <comment id="236274" author="adilger" created="Sat, 3 Nov 2018 07:18:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just to clarify, a 16TiB MDT is not considered a &quot;large&quot; MDT, so it shouldn&apos;t need the  &quot;&lt;tt&gt;64bit&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; or &quot;&lt;tt&gt;extents&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; feature, since all 2^32 4KB blocks can be addressed without the use of extents.  For MDTs that do not store data, the use of extents reduces directory efficiency somewhat and is intentionally disabled.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It isn&apos;t clear why mke2fs 1.44 is complaining in this case, because the specified block count &lt;tt&gt;3106406400 = 0xb9280000&lt;/tt&gt; blocks is significantly less than 2^32 blocks.  If the blocks count was specified as exactly 2^32 (or 16TB) I&apos;d suggest to use a slightly smaller value to avoid this warning.  You could try to add &quot;&lt;tt&gt;--mkfsoptions=&quot;-O ^64bit&quot;&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; to remove the &lt;tt&gt;64bit&lt;/tt&gt; option in case this is being inherited from your environment?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
